

*Compile*
If your environment variables are set correctly (see /lbne/app/users/lblpwg_tools/globes_setup.sh on lbnegpvm01) then you should just be able to run "make sigdcp"



*Running*
An example command:
~/lbne-lblpwgtools/trunk/code/globes-tools/sigdcp/sigdcp -DBEAMENERGY=120 -DNUBARTIME=5 -DLAMASS=30 -DNUTIME=5 -DBEAMPOWER=700 -p '0.593,0.154,0.705,0,0.0000758,0.00235' -E '0.03,0.03,0.11,0,0.03,0.05' -T3 numi810_v2_nodis.glb numi810_anti_v2_nodis.glb ~/lbne-lblpwgtools/trunk/code/globes-tools/sigdcp/altsAnalysis_mh/alts_ashriver_30kt_nodis.dat&

-T3 specificies that mass hiearchy sensitivities are to be generated. For now, read the source for other options.

More to follow...
